Class MFQ

  • java.lang.Object
    • MFQ

  • public class MFQ
extends java.lang.Object
    MFQ class that runs the simulation. The class runs the simulation in a loop very closely to the flowchart provided for the lab. MFQ will tick the clock, submit Job objects from the input queue into queue 1, check if the Cpu class's busyflag is true/false, decrement/increment Clock and Cpu class variables, Preempt Jobs from the Cpu and put them into the next lowest level queue, and submit jobs to the Cpu. MFQ will also output messages for events such as an arrival or departure from the queuing network.
    Version:
    4/5/2019
    Author:
    Joshua Matson id# 012024010
